<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-22T02:20:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-20T22:00:00-05:00" n="776" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 195.1/62</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Rio de Janeiro</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BAL1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Burnell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Rio De Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-09-22T02:20:00-05:00" notBefore="1914-09-21T00:00:00-03:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September
                                22, 1914, 2:20 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>The British Consul states that acting under instructions from the British
                            Legation he cannot until so instructed close register of steamer <persName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Robert Dollar</hi></persName>. British Legation is
                            awaiting instructions in the premises from London.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BAL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Burnell</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>